@@eThe Cinderteeth Mountains -- Quarantine Ledger Hazard Assessment@@N

The @@rQuarantine Ledger@@N maintains a permanent advisory on the
Cinderteeth range. Classification: @@rSystemic Supply Chain Threat,
Tier One@@N. No other geographic feature has disrupted Mafdet's
commerce as consistently or as catastrophically.

The @@rAshfall@@N is not ancient history to our Ledger Houses. It is
the @@yevent that wrote our emergency protocols@@N. When ash poisoned
wells and streams, the inland trade network collapsed for years.
Caravans stopped. The oasis corridor dried up -- not of water, but
of goods. Our harbor sat open and empty. The @@ySand-Sea Carters'
Guild@@N nearly dissolved during the second Ash Winter.

We rebuilt. But every Hazard Scribe knows the lesson: @@dvolcanic
risk is supply chain risk@@N. A caldera that erupts in the western
mountains empties our eastern docks three seasons later.

The @@WSpirebound Conclave's@@N abandoned @@lresonance crystals@@N in the
Bellspine ridge are @@runattested artifacts of unknown function@@N.
None have been cataloged, because the Conclave collapsed without
filing a single manifest. Under the Dual-Attestation Protocol, any
crystal fragment reaching our port from the Cinderteeth requires
Tier Three quarantine -- inland provenance unverifiable, maritime
risk classification @@rhigh-unknown@@N.

The @@yVentspeakers@@N who once read volcanic behavior interest our
Harbor Wardens as a lost early-warning network. Their polished
@@dname-stones@@N at vent mouths function as attestation markers --
proof that someone maintained a watching relationship with specific
vents. That relationship is broken. No one reads the mountain's
moods with their rigor.

The @@yHazard Doctrine@@N practiced at mountain route houses -- the
@@WSilent Bell Protocol@@N, the @@rdouble-water doctrine@@N -- is sound
logistics discipline. Our own harbor chain operates on similar
principles: when conditions change, halt, verify, and proceed only
under attestation. The mountain people learned this from disaster.
@@ySo did we.@@N

The @@rAsh Cult's@@N claim that eruptions are divine verdicts is the
kind of unattested assertion the Shrine of the First Claw was built
to reject. @@dThe mountain does not judge. It erupts. The difference
matters.@@N
